congress.#text: One Hundred Thirteenth Congress of the United States of America

official-title.#text: To direct the Secretary of the Interior to continue stocking fish in certain lakes in the North Cascades National Park, Ross Lake National Recreation Area, and Lake Chelan National Recreation Area.

role.#text: Speaker of the House of Representatives.
Vice President of the United States and President of the Senate.

text.#text: This Act may be cited as the

term.#tail: means collectively the North Cascades National Park, Ross Lake National Recreation Area, and Lake Chelan National Recreation Area.
term.#text: North Cascades National Park Service Complex

header.#text: North cascades national park service complex

quote.#text: North Cascades National Park Service Complex Mountain Lakes Fishery Management Plan and Environmental Impact Statement

header.#text: Stocking of certain lakes in the north cascades national park service complex

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#tail: shall authorize the stocking of fish in lakes in the North Cascades National Park Service Complex.
is authorized to allow stocking of fish in not more than 42 of the 91 lakes in the North Cascades National Park Service Complex that have historically been stocked with fish.
shall only stock fish that are—

text.#text: native to the slope of the Cascade Range on which the lake to be stocked is located; and
nonreproducing, as identified in management alternative B of the plan.

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#tail: shall consider relevant scientific information, including the plan and information gathered under subsection (c).

text.#text: In making fish stocking decisions under this Act, the

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#tail: shall coordinate the stocking of fish under this Act with the State of Washington.

text.#text: continue a program of research and monitoring of the impacts of fish stocking on the resources of the applicable unit of the North Cascades National Park Service Complex; and

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#text: Committee on Energy and Natural Resources of the Senate

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#tail: a report that describes the results of the research and monitoring under paragraph (1).
